Linux
-----
Install the libxml2 development headers via your package manager:

  # Debian / Ubuntu
  sudo apt-get install libxml2-dev

  # Fedora / RHEL / CentOS
  sudo dnf install libxml2-devel

Then install the package:

  install.packages("XBRL", repos = NULL, type = "source")


macOS
-----
libxml2 ships with macOS. If the development headers are missing, install
via Homebrew:

  brew install libxml2

Then install the package:

  install.packages("XBRL", repos = NULL, type = "source")


Windows
-------
Building from source requires Rtools (https://cran.r-project.org/bin/windows/Rtools/)
and a libxml2 build. Set LIB_XML to the root of your libxml2 installation
before building:

  Sys.setenv(LIB_XML = "C:/path/to/libxml2")
  install.packages("XBRL", repos = NULL, type = "source")

